<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-10T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-10T08:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EAC/11–1044: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gallman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-10T14:00:00+01:00">November
                                    10, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 10—11:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>9785. For the Under Secretary and Mr. Dunn. Reference Embassy’s 9776,
                            November 9, 8 p.m. British Chiefs of Staff have today officially stated
                            their opinion, reported to Mosely by Strang, that the interim amendment
                            regarding Bremen is acceptable for inclusion in the Protocol on Zones
                            provided the words “he determines” can be changed to “may be agreed”. As
                            this question was presented fully in 9776 the Department’s comments and
                            instructions will be awaited.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gallman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>